  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nOur Pyrmont node did not apply the new config merged in https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/2975\r\n\r\nThe cause is that the cli beacon cmd had persisted a `config.yaml` in the rootDir with these values\r\n\r\n```\r\n'PRESET_BASE': 'mainnet'\r\n'MIN_GENESIS_ACTIVE_VALIDATOR_COUNT': '16384'\r\n'MIN_GENESIS_TIME': '1605700800'\r\n'GENESIS_FORK_VERSION': '0x00002009'\r\n'GENESIS_DELAY': '432000'\r\n'ALTAIR_FORK_VERSION': '0x01000000'\r\n'ALTAIR_FORK_EPOCH': '18446744073709551615'\r\n'MERGE_FORK_VERSION': '0x02000000'\r\n'MERGE_FORK_EPOCH': '18446744073709551615'\r\n'SHARDING_FORK_VERSION': '0x03000000'\r\n'SHARDING_FORK_EPOCH': '18446744073709551615'\r\n'TRANSITION_TOTAL_DIFFICULTY': '4294967296'\r\n'SECONDS_PER_SLOT': '12'\r\n'SECONDS_PER_ETH1_BLOCK': '14'\r\n'MIN_VALIDATOR_WITHDRAWABILITY_DELAY': '256'\r\n'SHARD_COMMITTEE_PERIOD': '256'\r\n'ETH1_FOLLOW_DISTANCE': '2048'\r\n'INACTIVITY_SCORE_BIAS': '4'\r\n'INACTIVITY_SCORE_RECOVERY_RATE': '16'\r\n'EJECTION_BALANCE': '16000000000'\r\n'MIN_PER_EPOCH_CHURN_LIMIT': '4'\r\n'CHURN_LIMIT_QUOTIENT': '65536'\r\n'DEPOSIT_CHAIN_ID': '5'\r\n'DEPOSIT_NETWORK_ID': '5'\r\n'DEPOSIT_CONTRACT_ADDRESS': '0x8c5fecdc472e27bc447696f431e425d02dd46a8c'\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the command starts again, reads this config and overwrites the new default values with those. Note that it includes `ALTAIR_FORK_EPOCH`.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n- If the user hasn't explicitly customized a config we **should not** persist the defaults. It will prevent our nodes from forking to altair in existing networks.\r\n- I'm not even sure that we should persist the config file at all. We have to expose an option for users to provide a custom config file, but what's the point storing it if the user doesn't need to? Note that this routine comes back from when we used a two step process with init then run.\r\n- Add more logging in the beacon node about current fork:\r\n  - On start, the cli should log the current fork\r\n  - When a fork transition happens, the chain should log that\r\n  - Metrics must include a text field with the current fork name\r\n\r\n",
